race.description: Book Your X-mas Party @ Plrc 4YO+ Handicap
race.comment: Very competitive. SETTEVELI (4) is one of several for the Dunn/Bishop team and although facing a long drought looks well placed first try this circuit. Rarely far away at the provincials and only needs to bring those figures here to feature. Drawn for a soft run and will wind up late. BULLS ON PARADE (8) is a fairly lightly raced galloper having first run for the new local yard. Doesn't win out of turn but rates well this line-up and can open his account with a big run. SHUTTLE RUN (6) got well back and ran on hard to score at Clare last time in a busy finish. That was the first run for the new yard and can measure up again. HAYZEE FANTAYZEE (12) was beaten just a neck by SHUTTLE RUN at Clare, also hitting the line hard from well back to just miss. Fitter and is a win chance this line-up. MORE SUGAR (5) is a mare resuming from a good spell and has placed 3/7 fresh. Already a winner here and worth including.
